{"key":"post-9531257","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9531257</id>\n<content>Make the holes about 2 inches apart (5 cm) on all six sides.&amp;nbsp; Use a 1/4&quot; drill bit(6mm).&amp;nbsp; If you drill the holes too large it will require much more frequent misting.&amp;nbsp; Don't use a 3/8&quot; drill bit.&amp;nbsp; A 3/8&quot; hole has more than twice as much area as a 1/4&quot; hole.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you make it as directed, the perlite won't dry out for at least 6 weeks, which is plenty of time for a cropping cycle, at which time you rinse, drain, and return the perlite to service.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9531524</next>\n<prev>9531231</prev>\n<first>9530443</first>\n<last>9607261</last>\n<when>1230911956</when>\n<utime>01/02/09 05:59 PM</utime>\n</post>"}